# ripplegraph workflow - host agent guide

This document is the protocol contract for any host agent driving this
workflow via the `ripplegraph` CLI. The filesystem state is authoritative.

## Commands

Use these commands from the workflow root:

```sh
ripplegraph validate --workflow-root .
ripplegraph start --graph <graph-id> --workflow-root .
ripplegraph state --workflow-root .
ripplegraph step --output '<json>' --workflow-root .
ripplegraph suspend --note "pause current work" --workflow-root .
ripplegraph resume --run-id <run-id> --workflow-root .
ripplegraph abandon --workflow-root .
```

## Loop

1. Run `ripplegraph state --workflow-root .`.
2. Read the current node purpose, instructions, and output schema.
3. Do the work requested by the node.
4. Submit JSON with `ripplegraph step --output '<json>' --workflow-root .`.
5. Continue until the run reaches a terminal node.

## Switching work

Only one run is current at a time. To change focus, suspend the current run and
start or resume another run. Do not edit `current.json` by hand unless the CLI
cannot recover.

## Files

```sh
workflow.json
current.json
runs/<run-id>/checkpoint.json
runs/<run-id>/transition-log.jsonl
```

If conversation memory conflicts with these files, trust the files.

